In a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Sarah Sanders discussed various topics including the Winter Olympics, North Korea, school safety, and the Trump administration's position on gun control. Sanders expressed support for the permanent denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula and emphasized that any dialogue with North Korea must lead to denuclearization. She also announced that President Trump will host President Macron of France on April 24th for the first state visit of the Trump administration. Regarding school safety, Sanders stated that the President wants to make schools a harder target for attackers and is open to ideas from Americans of all backgrounds and beliefs. She mentioned that the President supports strengthening background checks and banning bump stocks. However, she did not provide details on whether the President supports universal background checks or raising the age limit for gun ownership. Sanders also commented on the recent guilty plea of Rick Gates, stating that the actions occurred before Gates was involved with the President's campaign.